      • KeyStorage

        public KeyStorage(CryptoFile file)
           throws GbayCryptoException
        Generate a KeyStorage from a file.

        Note: If p12 is having pin you need to set Pin in CryptoFile . 

         -- Example : loading test.pfx which it's pfx pin is 12345678
 
 CryptoFile file = new CryptoFile(new File("test.pfx"), "12345678");
 KeyStorage ks = new KeyStorage(file);

        Parameters:
        file - p12 file. Later on we may need to have other key stores supported but now, just pfx
        Throws:
        GbayCryptoException
        See Also:
        CryptoFile.setPin(char[]), tools.pki.gbay.util.general.CryptoFile#AegisFile(java.io.File, String)
